HEADWORD: Morbifical
<hw>Mor*bif"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>morbus</ets> disease +
<ets>-ficare</ets> (in comp.) to make: cf. F. <ets>morbifique</ets>. See
<er>-fy</er>.]</ety> <def>Causing disease; generating a sickly state;
<as>as, a <ex>morbific</ex> matter</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

